@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@email = authtest@example.com
@password = Pass@123

### Run order:
### 1) Run Register once. If it already exists, continue to Login.
### 2) Run Login, then Create, Get, Update.

### 1) Register a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Auth Test User",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "role": "user"
}

### 2) Login and capture JWT token
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 3) Create ticket (protected route)
# @name createTicket
POST {{baseUrl}}/tickets
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.$.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Auth middleware test",
  "description": "Ticket created from REST Client .http file",
  "status": "Open"
}

### 4) Get tickets (protected route)
GET {{baseUrl}}/tickets
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.$.token}}

### 5) Update ticket (uses created ticket id automatically)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/tickets/{{createTicket.response.body.$._id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.$.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "In Progress"
}

### 6) Negative test - no token (should return 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/tickets
